---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../css/services.css";
---

<Layout
  title="Electronic Systems | GeneralSoft UAE"
  description="Expert electronic systems and IoT development services in the UAE. Smart devices, embedded systems, IoT infrastructure, and connected solutions."
  path="/services/electronic-systems/"
  image="/img/og-electronic-systems.jpg"
>
  <section class="service-content" id="software-services">
    <div class="service-section" style="margin-top: 120px;">
      <h2 class="service-title">Electronic Systems & IoT</h2>
      <p>
        The Internet of Things is transforming industries across the UAE — from
        smart buildings in Dubai to connected healthcare facilities and
        industrial automation in Abu Dhabi. At GeneralSoft, we design and build
        electronic systems that bridge the physical and digital worlds. Our
        expertise spans IoT architecture, embedded systems, sensor integration,
        and real-time data processing.
      </p>
      <p>
        We work with the full IoT technology stack: from firmware and edge
        computing to cloud ingestion, data lakes, and analytics dashboards. Our
        team has hands-on experience with LoRaWAN, 5G, BLE, MQTT, and multiple
        cloud IoT platforms.
      </p>

      <h3>Electronic Systems Capabilities</h3>
      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>IoT Architecture & Infrastructure</h4>
          <p>
            End-to-end IoT solutions from sensor selection and device management
            to cloud ingestion and analytics.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Embedded Systems</h4>
          <p>
            Firmware development for microcontrollers, Raspberry Pi, and custom
            embedded hardware with real-time processing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Smart Building & Automation</h4>
          <p>
            Connected building systems including asset tracking, environmental
            monitoring, and predictive maintenance.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-box">
          <h4>Industrial IoT (IIoT)</h4>
          <p>
            OPC-UA integration, industrial sensor networks, and real-time
            monitoring for manufacturing and logistics.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Projects Proof Section -->
      <div class="projects-proof">
        <h3>Proven IoT Delivery — Projects Completed</h3>
        <p>
          Our IoT portfolio includes clinical asset tracking, cloud IoT
          platforms, and connected mobile applications with real-world
          deployments.
        </p>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Integrated Clinical ERP with IoT Asset Tracking</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Nov 2019 – Dec 2020</span>
            <span class="role">Azure Architect / PM / Tech Lead</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Integrated IoT asset tracking with Azure IoT Hub for real-time
            medical equipment monitoring in a clinical environment. Used
            LoRaWAN and BLE for device connectivity, with 5G for high-bandwidth
            data transmission. The system tracked equipment location, usage
            patterns, and maintenance schedules, sending automated notifications
            for preventive maintenance. Integrated with HoloLens (AR) for
            immersive equipment data visualization.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">Azure IoT Hub</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">LoRaWAN</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">5G</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">BLE</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">HoloLens AR</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">IoT</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Cloud Best Practices — IoT & Big Data POCs</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Feb 2017 – Jul 2017</span>
            <span class="role">Architect / PM / Tech Lead</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Built IoT proof-of-concept systems across multiple cloud platforms
            (Azure, AWS, GCP, IBM). Implemented IoT device management via MQTT
            protocols connecting Azure IoT Hub, Facebook, and AdaFruit IO.
            Worked with both virtual and physical IoT devices for sending and
            receiving notifications. Integrated SigFox and LoRaWAN for
            low-power wide-area network connectivity. Used Raspberry Pi with LTE
            for edge computing prototypes.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">MQTT</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Azure IoT Hub</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">SigFox</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">LoRaWAN</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Raspberry Pi</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">LTE</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>Recycling App with IoT Smart Bin Integration</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Apr 2023 – Aug 2023</span>
            <span class="role">Developer</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Integrated IoT sensors with a mobile recycling application for smart
            bin connectivity. Sensors monitored bin fill levels, temperature,
            and location, transmitting data via MQTT to the cloud. The mobile
            app displayed real-time bin status and guided users to the nearest
            available recycling point.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">IoT Sensors</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">MQTT</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Flutter</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Firebase</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Smart Bins</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project-card">
          <h4>IoT Deployment via CI/CD Pipeline</h4>
          <div class="project-meta">
            <span class="date">Jan 2016 – Mar 2016</span>
            <span class="role">Architect & Tech Lead</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            Implemented zero-touch continuous deployment for IoT device
            firmware and configuration. Built automated CI/CD pipelines using
            TFS 2015 Release Management that deployed IoT software updates
            across device fleets. The pipeline handled device provisioning,
            configuration management, and over-the-air (OTA) firmware updates.
          </p>
          <div class="tech-tags">
            <span class="tech-tag">CI/CD</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">IoT</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">TFS 2015</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">PowerShell</span>
            <span class="tech-tag">Azure</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>IoT Technology Stack</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cloud IoT Platforms:</strong> Azure IoT Hub, AWS IoT Core, IBM Watson IoT</li>
        <li><strong>Protocols:</strong> MQTT 5.0, AMQP 1.0, OPC-UA, LoRaWAN, BLE, 5G</li>
        <li><strong>Edge Computing:</strong> Raspberry Pi, Azure IoT Edge, AWS Greengrass</li>
        <li><strong>Messaging:</strong> Apache Kafka, RabbitMQ, Azure Event Hubs</li>
        <li><strong>Data & Analytics:</strong> Azure Data Lake, Power BI, Time Series Insights</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faq-container">
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <p class="section-subtitle">
          Common questions about our electronic systems and IoT services.
        </p>

        <div class="faq-list">
          <details>
            <summary>What IoT connectivity options do you support?</summary>
            <p>
              We support a wide range of connectivity options including Wi-Fi,
              BLE, LoRaWAN, 5G, LTE-M, NB-IoT, and SigFox. The right choice
              depends on your use case — power consumption, range, bandwidth,
              and cost requirements. We help you select the optimal connectivity
              for your specific application.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Can you integrate IoT with our existing ERP or CRM?</summary>
            <p>
              Yes. IoT data is most valuable when it connects to your business
              systems. We integrate IoT data streams with ERP systems (SAP,
              Dynamics 365), CRM platforms, and analytics dashboards so that
              sensor data drives real business decisions and automated workflows.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you build custom IoT hardware?</summary>
            <p>
              We design and prototype custom IoT solutions using off-the-shelf
              hardware (Raspberry Pi, Arduino, ESP32) and can coordinate with
              manufacturing partners for custom PCB design and production when
              needed. Our focus is on the full system — hardware selection,
              firmware, connectivity, cloud, and application layers.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="contact" id="contact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="contact-content">
        <h2>Let's Build Something Great Together</h2>
        <p>
          Ready to connect your business with IoT? Get in touch with our
          team today.
        </p>
        <div class="contact-info">
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">🌐</div><strong>Website</strong><a
              href="https://generalsoft.ae">generalsoft.ae</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <a href="/contact/"
              ><div class="contact-item-icon">📧</div><strong>Contact Us</strong
              ><br />Get in touch</a
            >
          </div>
          <div class="contact-item">
            <div class="contact-item-icon">📍</div><strong>Location</strong
            ><span>Ras Al Khaimah</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
